Subject: Legacy Contract Reinforcement Policy 099

Description: SOP-HG realization event for keeping older or less articulated SOP contracts as reinforcement rather than authority.

& [LegacyContractReinforcementPolicy_099] is the realized periphery event
  + [event_status] is realized
  + [event_time] is 2026-06-25
  + [focus_subject] is Legacy Contract Reinforcement Policy
  + [source_question] is how to keep overbuilt remnants of older SOP contracts from acting as authority while still allowing them to reinforce current primary impulses when they agree
  + [primary_realization] is legacy contracts should remain available as lineage, periphery, search clues, and corroboration, but only the current source-preserved, canonical, focal, registry, manager, and proof-bearing layer acts as primary authority
  + [refinement_realization] is no-agreement legacy material is baseless or off-topic, while wide shared context with partial agreement can mark a possible blind spot to inspect without becoming authority
  + [primary_authority_layer] is current user direction, preserved source, active canonical contract, focal point, registry frame, manager state, validation, commit, and push
  + [legacy_contract] is older, thinner, imported, seed, backup, or less articulated SOP material
  + [reinforcement_use] is allowed only after agreement_test passes
  + [blind_spot_candidate] is allowed only when shared context is wide and partial agreement exists
  + [articulation_gap] is preserved when old material is useful but not precise enough to govern
  + [wisdom_register] is this policy lets the framework keep its history without letting old half-formed rails pull authority away from the active articulation
  + [caution_register] is less articulated old instructions must not bypass newer boundaries, gates, source preservation, validation, or user direction
  + [balance_register] is stable because authority, reinforcement, lineage, search clues, caution debt, and outside remain distinct
  + [utility_horizon] is cleaner interpretation of older SOP remnants, safer refactors, better browser authority panels, and reduced overbuild interference
  + [next_step] is keep Task_161 ready while applying this policy whenever old contracts agree or conflict with active primary layers
  + [outside] is stale backup authority, legacy override, authority by age, authority by volume, hidden model preference, and unreviewed imported state

  = must: treat legacy support as reinforcement only after agreement_test
  = must: treat no-agreement material as baseless or off-topic
  = must: treat wide shared context plus partial agreement as blind spot review, not authority
  = must: route conflicts through Caution
  = should: preserve old contracts as lineage unless a separate refactor task selects them

